    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        public int getValue()
        Gets the value of TruckRestriction.Type restriction. Use TruckRestriction.hasValue() to check whether current type has any value associated with it.

        Value for each TruckRestriction.Type represents certain thing: TruckRestriction.Type.WEIGHT_RESTRICTION - maximum weight for truck in kg. TruckRestriction.Type.HEIGHT_RESTRICTION - maximum height for truck in cm. TruckRestriction.Type.LENGTH_RESTRICTION - maximum length for truck in cm. TruckRestriction.Type.WIDTH_RESTRICTION - maximum width for truck in cm. TruckRestriction.Type.WEIGHT_PER_AXLE_RESTRICTION - maximum kg per axel. TruckRestriction.Type.KPRA_LENGTH_RESTRICTION - kingpin to rear axle limit in cm. TruckRestriction.Type.SPEED_LIMIT - maximum speed in meters per second.

        Types below do not have any value associated with it: TruckRestriction.Type.PREFERRED_ROUTE TruckRestriction.Type.HAZMAT_PERMIT_REQUIRED TruckRestriction.Type.TRUCK_RESTRICTION TruckRestriction.Type.TOLL

        Returns:
        value for this type of restriction.

      • hasValue

        public boolean hasValue()
        Checks whether TruckRestriction.getType() has any value associated with it. Types such as TruckRestriction.Type.PREFERRED_ROUTE, TruckRestriction.Type.HAZMAT_PERMIT_REQUIRED, TruckRestriction.Type.TRUCK_RESTRICTION or TruckRestriction.Type.TOLL do not have value. All the other types should have value.
        Returns:
        True if this restriction has value, false otherwise.
